data.value:
Marsilya is a port city in the South-east of France. marsilya , which was selected as the European Capital of Culture in 2013, is the city where you will feel the Mediterranean identity in France. In the second largest city of France, the ancient Roman ruins and the medieval architecture are full. The Ionians departed from İzmir Foça in 600 BC and settled on the shores of Marsilya . ”This city was founded in 600 BC by the Phokaians from Anatolia Ph writes the brass plate in the Port of Marsilya .
You can take a tour in the historic old harbor where the castles meet, take a rest in the cafes lined up by the sea and take your memories to your loved ones in the small shops in the surrounding area. Take a stroll in Borely Park, one of the most beautiful parks in France.
